column1: OMAP-19: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Tonsil with IBEX

column2: (In preparation, update when submitted to bioRxiv)

column24: rationale

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by many subsets of myeloid cells (tingible body macrophages, proinflammatory M1 macrophages, dendritic cells). This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Defines perifollicular macrophages in the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Used to detect CD163.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels several subsets of T helper cells including CD4+ T cells, T regulatory cells, and T follicular helper cells. This marker is also expressed on myeloid cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

Defines germinal center based on enrichment of PD-1+ T follicular helper cells in this anatomical structure. This marker is critical for evaluating antigen experienced T cells and, when combined with other markers (CTLA-4, Tim-3, Lag-3), can define T cell exhaustion. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Used to detect PDCD1.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels cytotoxic T cells in the paracortex that are generally absent from B cell follicles. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

This marker is absent or lowly expressed in normal tonsil tissue but abundant in angiogenic tumor samples. This antibody was validated in ovarian cancer biopsy samples and is not a prioritized target for the tonsil OMAP.
Defines lymphatic vessels around the follicles of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
This marker defines the vasculature of the tonsil and targets an essential marker for blood endothelial cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

This marker is absent or lowly expressed in normal tonsil tissue but abundant in angiogenic tumor samples. This antibody was validated in ovarian cancer biopsy samples and is not a prioritized target for the tonsil OMAP.

Alpha smooth muscle actin defines the fibroblastic reticular network and vasculature of the tonsil. This is an essential marker for many cell types including smooth muscle cells and many subsets of fibroblasts. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it targets an essential marker for T regulatory cells and T follicular regulatory cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Defines T cell zone and is an essential marker of T cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Used to detect CD3E.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels several subsets of myeloid cells including macrophages/monocytes (CD11b+CD14+HLA-DR+) and granulocytes (CD11b+CD15+). It also labels follicular dendritic cells (CD11b+CD14+) in the B cell follicles. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Used to detect FUT4.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels macrophages/monocytes (CD11b+CD14+HLA-DR+) and follicular dendritic cells (CD11b+CD14+) in the B cell follicles. This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

This marker defines major anatomical structures including primary and secondary B cell follicles, the interfollicular region, and paracortex. This marker is expressed by B cells (HLA-DR+), GC B cells (HLA-DR++), and dendritic cells (HLA-DR++). This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels several subsets of myeloid cells including macrophages/monocytes (CD11b+CD14+HLA-DR+) and granulocytes (CD11b+CD15+). It also labels follicular dendritic cells (CD11b+CD14+) in the B cell follicles. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

column4: KRT10, KRT14, KRT15, KRT16, KRT19, KRT1, KRT2, KRT3, KRT4, KRT5, KRT7, KRT8
column24: Defines major anatomical structures of the tonsil including stratified squamous epithelium and tonsillar crypts. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD11c is expressed on dendritic cells in the paracortex and tingible body macrophages in the germinal center. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Defines B cell follicles and is an essential marker of B cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Defines B cell follicles in secondary lymphoid organs. This is not a priority target for the tonsil OMAP but useful for detecting tertiary lymphoid structures associated with cancer.
Used to detect CXCR5.
